fields.label: As your employer, WesTrac Pty Ltd (including any related body corporate) (“WesTrac”) takes seriously, and has obligations to ensure, your health and safety while at work. Accordingly, WesTrac may have collected, or may seek to collect, health information about you to the extent it will better enable WesTrac to facilitate your health and safety while you are at work.

groups.label: WesTrac may use health information it holds about you to ensure it is meeting its obligations to provide you with a healthy and safe work environment including the facilitation of any health-related requirements you may have related to the work you perform for WesTrac.

In the course of your employment with WesTrac, you may be required to undertake work at the premises of a WesTrac business partner, customer, or their respective contractors (“Customer”). For WesTrac to ensure that your health and safety is protected while undertaking work at the Customer’s premises, WesTrac may need to disclose health information it holds about you to the Customer. In doing so, WesTrac will only disclose health information about you to the extent it is reasonably necessary to enable the Customer to ensure your health and safety, and facilitate any health-related requirements you may have, in light of the nature of the work you will be required to perform while on the Customer’s premises.

Except for the uses and disclosures described above or any other use and disclosure required by law, WesTrac will not otherwise use or disclose your health information and will take all reasonable steps to keep the health information it holds about you confidential and secure.

Please sign this form to evidence your consent to WesTrac collecting, using and disclosing to Customers, health information it holds about you in circumstances described in this statement. Please note that in the absence of you providing your consent:
You may be unable to undertake your role with WesTrac or work at a Customer’s premises;
You may be required to undertake a modified role or perform modified work while at a Customer’s premises;
or
Your health information may nevertheless be used by WesTrac or disclosed to a Customer where WesTrac is lawfully required to do so under applicable work health and safety, or other, laws.
